Success Criteria
Technical success will be demonstrated by a functioning prototype that supports project stakeholder interaction, consistent context management, requirements capture and potentially project configuration. Stakeholder satisfaction will be measured with feedback from industry expert Morgan Worrell. This project represents a Capstone experience for the Software Engineering Graduate program at Regis University. As such program learning success will be evaluated by the team’s demonstrated synthesis of requirements engineering, project management, architectural design principles and technical implementation. Portfolio success will be assessed by the project’s suitability for demonstration.
Appendix A: Project Selection Process
Each team member brought three potential project ideas to the kickoff meeting to form a pool of twelve possibilities. During the meeting we discussed the pros, cons, feasibility and risks of the twelve choices and narrowed the list to the top five contenders. Then we performed a ranked choice vote to choose the winner and confirmed everyone was happy with that choice.
